Westlands MP Timothy Wanyonyi has urged the government to allocate more funds to the elderly.He also urged children to take care of their aging parents. &ldquo;People with parents above 60 years should learn to appreciate their parents. Do not take your parents to homes. However sick and dirty they might be, they are your parents,&rdquo; Wanyonyi said.He spoke at Highridge Secondary School after donating food, clothing and bedding to the elderly.Wanyonyi urged residents to keep healthy to avoid lifestyle diseases.In June 2011, then Finance minister Uhuru Kenyatta announced an increase in the money allocated to the elderly and orphans.NGO Help Age estimates that 80 per cent of the elderly do not have access to a regular income.